  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "I understand your frustration with the account opening delay at Zerodha. Here\u2019s how you can escalate the issue effectively:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Support**: Start by reaching out to Zerodha's customer support again. Use their official support ticketing system or call their helpline to explain your situation clearly, emphasizing the delay beyond the promised timeline.\n\n2. **Email Communication**: Send a detailed email to their support team (usually support@zerodha.com) outlining your situation, including your application number, and stating that it has been 10 days since your submission and you have not received any updates.\n\n3. **Social Media**: You can also contact Zerodha through their social media platforms like Twitter or Facebook. Companies often respond quickly to public messages. Make sure to tag them and describe your issue politely but clearly.\n\n4. **Escalation Matrix**: Look for an escalation matrix on their website or in their help section. They may provide direct email addresses or contacts for higher-level support.\n\n5. **Local Investor Associations**: If the issue is still unresolved, consider reaching out to local investment or retail investor associations. They may provide assistance or escalate your grievance.\n\n6. **Visit the Office**: If possible, visit a local Zerodha office or their headquarters to discuss your issue in person.\n\nMake sure to keep documentation of all your communications for reference. Good luck!",
